"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly uses the `sns.lmplot` function within the `g.map()` method. The `g.map()` method is intended to apply a plotting function that takes the data as its first argument, while `sns.lmplot` is a higher-level function that creates its own figure and axes. Instead, a suitable function like `sns.scatterplot` or `sns.regplot` should be used within `g.map()`.\",\n  \"patch\": \"6c6\\n< g.map(sns.lmplot, 'total_bill', 'tip')\\n---\\n> g.map(sns.regplot, 'total_bill', 'tip')\"\n}"